Snapshot can trigger transactions using tools like the Zodiac Reality module, but it still has issues with accurately getting transactions on-chain.

This guide will walk you through the steps of creating a Nouns DAO proposal. If you're unsure whether a proposal is the correct path for your idea to receive funding, please refer to this guide to ensure you're in the right place. If your idea is still in a nascent stage or the details haven't been fleshed out, you can get feedback in the <#875751366340005908> channel in the Nouns Discord.

**How To Write A Proposal**
Your proposal should communicate:
- What is the project
- How will it proliferate Nouns
- How much funding do you need
- How will the funds be used

We advise keeping this information at the top of your proposal, potentially as a TL;DR section. Submissions can quickly become quite long as implementation details are fleshed out, and readers will appreciate having this baseline info summarized up-front. It's in your interest to make the proposal easy to digest and get the gist of in seconds.

Below you'll find three well-rounded proposals that were successfully funded. They clearly communicated their idea with a simple overview, a timeline with milestones, and a cost breakdown.

**Post On Discourse**
Once you have all the details nailed down, you can post your proposal on the Nouns Discourse, a forum for longer-form proposal ideas. At the top, click the "+ New Topic" button and post your idea. Be sure to prefix the title with "Proposal: "to be easily identified as a proposal request. 

Now, fill in your content in the text field, including images. Feel free to save your progress and come back later. 

*(Please note that Discourse doesn't give editing privileges to new accounts until they've been active for a while, so if you make a mistake or typo in your proposal, you won't be able to change it. Instead, you can specify in the comments what was wrong.)*

**Sponsorship**
Only Noun owners (Nouners) can submit official proposals to the DAO for funding. If you don't own a Noun, you'll have to get a sponsor to put the proposal on-chain for you. You can connect with a sponsor by waiting for feedback on your Discourse post or via networking in the Discord. You can also try to get groups like The Nouncil or any of the Nouns' SubDAOs to sponsor your proposal.

**Getting Feedback**
This is the refinement phase. All proposals undergo budget and impact scrutiny, so don't be surprised if yours is too. The "refining fire" prepares your proposal for the voting period. This phase will help make sure your proposal is in great shape and won't be defeated for something that could've been easily avoided.

It's common to face push-back at this stage of the proposal, and we ask you to take criticism in stride. The goal is to make sure proposals effectively proliferate Nouns, and we want you to succeed.

**Voting Timeline**
Once your proposal is submitted, it will enter the Voting Week, which lasts for a minimum of seven days. When the proposal goes on-chain, its status will receive a 'pending' status. This is a 2-day window where proposals are public but cannot be voted on. Usually, the proposal attracts more attention at this point and is heavily discussed on Discord. 

Next, the status will change to 'active', and Noun holders can vote on it for the next three days. When the 'active' period ends, the proposal will either have succeeded or been defeated (barring cancellation or a veto). 

If the proposal succeeds, it will have to be manually queued for execution. This is done by connecting your wallet to nouns.wtf/vote, finding the prop, and clicking the "Queue Proposal ⌐◨-◨" button. Anyone can do this step, and there is a gas fee attached. When done, the status will be changed to 'queued', and after another two days of waiting, the proposal will be executed. Your proposal has been passed, and the building can begin!
